Package projects.pqueue.heaps

Class LinkedMinHeap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • projects.pqueue.heaps.LinkedMinHeap<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The Comparable type of object held by this.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, MinHeap<T>
    public class LinkedMinHeap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements MinHeap<T>

    A LinkedMinHeap is a tree (specifically, a complete binary tree) where every node is smaller than or equal to its descendants (as defined by the Comparable.compareTo(Object) overridings of the type T). Percolation is employed when the root is deleted, and insertions guarantee maintenance of the heap property in logarithmic time.

    You must edit this class! To receive any credit for the unit tests related to this class, your implementation must be a "linked", non-contiguous storage implementation based on a binary tree of nodes and references. Use the skeleton code we have provided to your advantage, but always remember that the only functionality our tests can test is public functionality.
